  <brief_title>Ultrasound Guidance Vs. Electrical Nerve Stimulation for Infraclavicular Brachial Plexus Block</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Rikshospitalet University Hospital</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Rikshospitalet University Hospital</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      In an observer-blinded study ultrasound guidance and electrical nerve stimulation will be
      compared for lateral sagital infraclavicular blocks (LSIB). Block effectiveness, time
      consumption and patient acceptance will be registered in 80 patients. Ultrasound guidance
      may cause less discomfort and could be less time consuming than electrical nerve
      stimulation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
